diff:1670614974:1670042851:=60,74c60%0a%3c #foxbegin 221209-194254-772760#%0a%3c (:div1 class=expansionhead:)%0a%3c !!!Categorization of Speakers %0a%3c -> - pwchan%0a%3c -> [-09.12.2022 - 11:42-]%0a%3c >>rfloat%3c%3c   %0a%3c (:if1 authgroup @tas:)%0a%3c {[foxdelrange button 221209-194254-772760 {$FullName} ]}%0a%3c (:if1end:)%0a%3c >>%3c%3c%0a%3c (:div1end:) %0a%3c >>messageitem%3c%3c %0a%3c The report used notes that people will often link groups with certain attitudes and beliefs. This link is a normal part of the cognitive process (stereotyping), so it occurs all the time. In everyday life, the results of such stereotyping may not be super important. However, in cases such as those provided, the consequences of such profiling can be unjust decisions and sentences in court. There are some who advocate for the more widespread usage of "standard" forms of English, but forcing people to use these forms of English could result in losses of culture and diversity in the way that Americans speak, along with losses of cultural identity as a whole for those who speak English in different forms, such as AAVE.%0a%3c >>%3c%3c%0a%3c #foxend 221209-194254-772760#%0a---%0a> %0a
